    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you dont have an entry point defined in your manifest invoking <code>java -jar foo.jar</code> will not work.</p>\n\n<p>Use this command if you dont have a manifest or to run a different main class than the one specified in the manifest:</p>\n\n<pre><code>java -cp foo.jar full.package.name.ClassName\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>See also instructions on how to create a manifest with an entry point:\n<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/deployment/jar/appman.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/deployment/jar/appman.html</a></p>\n"
